class.name: CATEwrEquipotential
class.abstract: This class is used to describe an equipotential.

data.name: Diameter
data.abstract: The Diameter attribute corresponds to an estimation of the diameter of the wires which will realize the equipotential.

data.name: Extremities
data.abstract: This list contains the identifier of the extremities of the equipotential.

data.name: Id
data.abstract: The identifier of the equipotential.

data.name: Name
data.abstract: The name of the equipotential.

data.name: RoutingPriority
data.abstract: The RoutingPriority attribute is used in equipotential routing.

data.name: SeparationCode
data.abstract: The SeparationCode attribute is used in knowledge rules checked in equipotential routing.

data.name: SubType
data.abstract: The subtype of the equipotential.

data.name: WirePartNumber
data.abstract: The WirePartNumber attribute corresponds to the part number of the wire which will realize the equipotential.

class.name: CATEwrWire
class.abstract: This class is used to describe a wire.

data.name: BendRadius
data.abstract: The BendRadius attribute corresponds to the maximum curvature of the wire.

data.name: Color
data.abstract: The color of the wire.

data.name: FatherWireGroup
data.abstract: The identifier of the WireGroup (if exists) immediate father of the wire.

data.name: Id
data.abstract: The identifier of the wire.

data.name: Id_FirstExtremity
data.abstract: The identifier of the first extremity.

data.name: Id_Harness
data.abstract: The identifier of the harness (if exists) containing the wire.

data.name: Id_SecondExtremity
data.abstract: The identifier of the second extremity.

data.name: InnerDiameter
data.abstract: The InnerDiameter attribute corresponds to the diameter of the conductor, excluding the insulation.

data.name: LinearMass
data.abstract: The LinearMass attribute corresponds to the linear mass of the wire.

data.name: Name
data.abstract: The name of the wire.

data.name: OuterDiameter
data.abstract: The OuterDiameter attribute corresponds to the diameter of the wire, including the insulation.

data.name: PartNumber
data.abstract: The PartNumber attribute corresponds to the part number of the wire.

data.name: SeparationCode
data.abstract: The SeparationCode attribute is used in knowledge rules checked in wire routing.

data.name: SubType
data.abstract: The subtype of the wire.

data.name: sSignalId
data.abstract: The SignalID of the wire routed.

data.name: BendRadius
data.abstract: The BendRadius attribute corresponds to the maximum curvature of the WireGroup.

data.name: Color
data.abstract: The color of the WireGroup.

data.name: Diameter
data.abstract: The Diameter attribute corresponds to the diameter of the WireGroup.

data.name: FatherWireGroup
data.abstract: The identifier of the WireGroup (if exists) immediate father of the WireGroup.

data.name: Id
data.abstract: The identifier of the WireGroup.

data.name: Id_FirstExtremity
data.abstract: The identifier of the first extremity of the Shielded Wire Group.

data.name: Id_Harness
data.abstract: The identifier of the harness (if exists) containing the WireGroup.

data.name: Id_SecondExtremity
data.abstract: The identifier of the second extremity of the Shielded Wire Group.

data.name: ListOfSubWireGroups
data.abstract: List of wire groups names children of the wire group.

data.name: ListOfSubWires
data.abstract: List of wire names children of the wire group.

data.name: Name
data.abstract: The name of the WireGroup.

data.name: PartNumber
data.abstract: The PartNumber attribute corresponds to the part number of the WireGroup.

data.name: SeparationCode
data.abstract: The SeparationCode attribute is used in knowledge rules checked in WireGroup routing.

data.name: SubType
data.abstract: The subtype of the WireGroup.

data.name: WireGroupType
data.abstract: Whether the Wire Group is Generic or Shielded.

data.name: WireLengthCoefficient
data.abstract: The WireLengthCoefficient attribute.

method.name: Filter
method.abstract: Filter a session for a given list of systems, a given list of criteria and a filtering option.

method.name: ResetFilter
method.abstract: Reset the session by reactivating every filtered objects.

class.name: CATIEwrRouteSegment
class.abstract: Interface on the route segment of wires or wire groups.

method.name: ListConductors
method.abstract: Fills a list of conductors going through a given network segment.

class.name: CATIEwrUipBundleSegment
class.abstract: Interface to manage bundle segment diameter.

method.name: ComputeBendRadius
method.abstract: Returns the value of bundle segment bend radius (in mm).

method.name: ComputeDiameter
method.abstract: Returns the value of a bundle segment diameter (in mm).

method.name: ListEquipotentials
method.abstract: Retrieves the list of equipotentials for a given system.

method.name: ListWireGroups
method.abstract: Retrieves the list of wire groups for a given list of systems and a given list of criteria.

method.name: ListWires
method.abstract: Retrieves the list of wires for a given list of systems and a given list of criteria.

class.name: CATIEwrWkbCfgAddin
class.abstract: Interface to add toolbars in the 'Electrical Wire Routing' workbench.

typedef.name: CATEwrFilterOption
typedef.abstract: The filtering option during filter process.
